C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:10:### Fixed — Asset Swap: cims / buildings / aircraft now reskin (#986)
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:11:- **Wrong swap archetypes for cims, buildings, and aircraft (live `0 succeeded` → `39 succeeded`)** — The #975 archetype guesses returned 0 RenderMesh-bearing entities, so the `RenderMesh AND <archetype>` swap query matched nothing and these categories logged `batch complete — 0 succeeded, 30 failed` while ground units swapped fine. A live entity-dump (bridge `queryEntities`, active skirmish) revealed the ground truth: (1) cims carry **`Components.Citizen`** (live count 58) with RenderMesh on the same entity — the previous guess `Components.Worker` matched only 2 singletons; (2) DINO **buildings** carry `Components.BuildingBase` (575) but **no RenderMesh on the parent** — the mesh lives on a CHILD entity referenced via `Unity.Entities.LinkedEntityGroup`; (3) `aerial_fighter` resolved to `DINOForge.Runtime.Aviation.AerialUnitComponent` which DINO never tags (0 live entities; no native fliers). Fixes: cims/worker/citizen → `Components.Citizen` (`PackStatMappings`); `aerial_fighter` swap archetype → `Components.SiegeUnit` (real renderable archetype, count 162; `AssetSwapSystem`); and a new `CollectRenderMeshChildren()` that, when a parent archetype carries no RenderMesh, walks `LinkedEntityGroup` to swap the RenderMesh-bearing children (`AssetSwapSystem`). Also: `GameControlCli` `entities` verb now prints the full JSON archetype dump. Live-verified after deploy: warfare-starwars pass `batch complete — 39 succeeded, 13 failed` (was 0 succeeded); `sw-cis-droid-pilot` cim `swapped 51/51 result=True`; `sw-cis-command-center` / `sw-cis-droid-factory` / `sw-clone-barracks` / `sw-rep-vehicle-bay` buildings each `swapped 100/100` via the child-walk. The 13 remaining failures are 90-byte STUB bundles with no usable mesh (pre-existing #101 asset gap), not archetype failures. Survey: `docs/sessions/entity-archetype-survey-20260531.md`. Files: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/PackStatMappings.cs`, `src/Tools/GameControlCli/Program.cs`.
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:76:- **AssetSwap THE "units look native" fix: mesh-substring filter was rejecting 100% of entities (#101).** Even after the reflection fix, every unit stayed native — live logs showed `swapped 0/100 entities (skipped 100 non-matching meshes)` for every mapping. Root cause: with an authoritative archetype filter already applied, the SECONDARY mesh-name substring filter (`VanillaMappingToMeshSubstrings`, e.g. `Swordsman`/`Militia`/`Knight`) was used as a hard *reject*, but those hand-guessed substrings do not match DINO's real mesh vocabulary (`swordsmen`, `royal_sword_2`, `bomj_*`, `harpy_*`, `undead_*`, `natives_*`), so 0 entities passed and no mesh was ever written. Fix: when an archetype filter is present it is authoritative — swap every entity the narrowed `EntityQuery` returns and ignore the substrings (which now serve only as a fallback targeting signal when there is no archetype filter). Live-verified: `swapped 100/100 … skipped 0` across MeleeUnit/RangeUnit/SiegeUnit/Aerial (66 positive swaps, 0 zero-swaps) — units now render their Star Wars meshes. (`src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`)
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:78:- **AssetSwap ground-unit swap: ComponentType→Int32 reflection error (#101, "units look native" BUG A).** `AssetSwapSystem.TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle`'s archetype-narrowed path threw at runtime — `Object of type 'Unity.Entities.ComponentType' cannot be converted to type 'System.Int32'` → `result=False` ("swapped 0/100" for ground units e.g. `sw-cis-magna-guard`). DINO's Unity 2021.3 `EntityManager` exposes the non-generic `GetSharedComponentData` in TWO overloads — `(Entity, ComponentType)` AND `(Entity, int typeIndex)` — and the `FirstOrDefault` lookup (which accepts either) could bind the Int32 overload, then invoking it with a boxed `ComponentType` threw. Fix: detect the bound overload's second-parameter type and pass `ComponentType.TypeIndex` (int) when it wants `System.Int32`, else the `ComponentType`. (`src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`)
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:79:- **AssetSwap aerial units: `aerial_fighter` no longer stuck in DIAGNOSTIC MODE (#101, BUG B).** `vanilla_mapping='aerial_fighter'` produced no archetype filter (PackStatMappings intentionally maps it to null for stat injection — `AerialSpawnSystem` owns aerial behaviour) AND no mesh-name substrings → `sw-tri-fighter`/`sw-nantex-fighter` skipped the swap. Fix: new `AssetSwapSystem.TryResolveSwapArchetype()` resolves `aerial_fighter` to `DINOForge.Runtime.Aviation.AerialUnitComponent` for the visual swap (PackStatMappings stays null so stat injection still defers to `AerialSpawnSystem`); added aerial mesh-name substrings (`Aerial/Air/Flying/Fighter/...`) as a fallback targeting signal so the swap proceeds even before `AerialSpawnSystem` tags the entity. (`src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/PackStatMappings.cs`)
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:81:- **AssetSwap buildings: structures no longer stuck in DIAGNOSTIC MODE (#101, building fix).** Pack buildings (e.g. `sw-cis-command-center`, `sw-rep-vehicle-bay`, `sw-cis-droid-factory`) registered their swap with **no** `vanilla_mapping` — `BuildingDefinition` had no such field and `ContentLoader` passed null — so every SW structure fell into DIAGNOSTIC MODE and kept rendering as the native royal/undead building. Fix: added `BuildingDefinition.VanillaMapping` (YAML `vanilla_mapping`); `ContentLoader` now passes it, defaulting to the generic `building` mapping when omitted; `AssetSwapSystem.TryResolveSwapArchetype()` maps `building` → `Components.BuildingBase` (the universal vanilla building archetype) and a `building` mesh-substring set was added as a refinement. Building stat injection is unaffected (resolution lives in the swap path, not `PackStatMappings`). (`src/SDK/Models/BuildingDefinition.cs`, `src/SDK/ContentLoader.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`)
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:84:- **Star Wars live mesh-swap exits DIAGNOSTIC MODE (#964).** `AssetSwapSystem.TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` previously referenced a non-existent `BundleToVanillaMeshMap` and tried to match optional mesh-name substrings by *bundle filename*, so every Star Wars bundle fell into DIAGNOSTIC MODE and no entity swap ran. The optional mesh-name refinement now keys off the request's `vanilla_mapping` value via `VanillaMappingToMeshSubstrings` (aligned 1:1 with `PackStatMappings.VanillaMappingToComponentType`). DIAGNOSTIC MODE is now entered only when there is **no** targeting signal at all — neither a resolved archetype filter nor mesh-name substrings — so a populated `vanilla_mapping` (already present on all 30 SW units; aerial intentionally skipped) lets the archetype-narrowed swap proceed. The mesh-name filter loop is guarded so archetype-only mode swaps every entity the narrowed query returns. Mesh/material lookup remains robust via `ResolveReplacementAssets` (exact-name → prefab renderer → `LoadAllAssets<Mesh>/<Material>` fallback — never the bundle key). Key audit: all 30 SW unit `visual_asset` keys resolve in `addressables.yaml`; 14 reference real (>40KB) bundles. Runtime builds netstandard2.0 exit 0; all 31 AssetSwap tests pass.
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:86:  - **Gap A — building swaps now register WITH a `vanilla_mapping`.** `ContentLoader.RegisterAssetSwaps` previously registered every building swap with a null `vanilla_mapping`, so the runtime `AssetSwapSystem` saw "no targeting signal" and skipped them in DIAGNOSTIC MODE. It now resolves a mapping per building in priority order — explicit `building.vanilla_mapping` → `building_type` (command/barracks/resource/defense/tower/wall/research) → generic `"building"` — and threads it into `AssetSwapRequest.VanillaMapping`. New `BuildingDefinition.VanillaMapping` (`vanilla_mapping:` YAML field) makes the targeting declarative.
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:89:  - `PackStatMappings.VanillaMappingToComponentType` gained entries for `cims`/`worker`/`citizen` (→ `Components.Worker`, candidate archetype — verify via entity dump) and `building`/`command`/`barracks`/`resource`/`economy`/`defense`/`tower`/`wall`/`research` (→ `Components.BuildingBase`). `AssetSwapSystem.VanillaMappingToMeshSubstrings` gained matching `bomj`/worker and building (castle/barrack/farm/tower/wall/…) mesh-name substrings so swaps still exit DIAGNOSTIC MODE via the secondary mesh-name filter when the archetype type does not resolve. Maps/skybox are Phase 2 (out of scope). Runtime builds netstandard2.0 exit 0; new registration + mapping tests added (`FullWorldConversionSwapTests`, `PackStatInjectorTests`).
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:120:  - **`GraphicsMaterialUpgrader` (`src/Runtime/Graphics/GraphicsMaterialUpgrader.cs`)** — `Upgrade(Material, assetKey)` produces a new `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit` material that carries over the base albedo map + tint and layers in declared PBR maps (albedo `_BaseMap`, metallic+gloss `_MetallicGlossMap`, normal `_BumpMap`, AO `_OcclusionMap`, emission `_EmissionMap`) with the matching shader keywords (`_METALLICSPECGLOSSMAP` / `_NORMALMAP` / `_OCCLUSIONMAP` / `_EMISSION`). Sets a sensible metallic/smoothness baseline even when no maps exist, so surfaces gain proper specular response under High. Graceful fallback to the original material when tier is Vanilla, when URP/Lit is unavailable, or on any error (never throws, never breaks a swap).
