C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:175:- **Star Wars bundles shipped primitive-placeholder prefabs instead of real meshes (#101/#947)** — The shipped `warfare-starwars` AssetBundles wired 64/75 bundle prefabs to Unity built-in primitive meshes (Cube/Capsule/Sphere, `fileID:10202`), so even a perfect in-game Harmony swap rendered cubes. Root cause: `*.fbx`/`*.glb`/`*.obj` are gitignored, so in a fresh worktree the only committed mesh source is `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/raw/<asset_id>/model.glb` (the `!packs/*/assets/raw/*/model.glb` allowlist); the intended pipeline (`convert_models.py` Blender GLB→FBX → `GenerateStarWarsPrefabsFromModels` → `BuildAssetBundles`) was never reproduced end-to-end in the worktree, and the primitive-only generators (`GenerateStarWarsPrefabs.cs`/`BuildAll.cs`, which *skip existing* prefabs) had poisoned the prefab dir. Fixes:
C:/Users/koosh/Dino/.claude/worktrees/envskybox/CHANGELOG.md:184:- **Aviation ECS systems crashed every frame: "This method should have been replaced by codegen"** — `AerialMovementSystem`, `AerialTargetingSystem`, and `AerialSpawnSystem` each used `Entities.ForEach(...).WithoutBurst().Run()` in their `OnUpdate`. `Entities.ForEach`/`Job.WithCode` REQUIRE the Unity.Entities DOTS source generator, which only runs inside the Unity Editor's compilation pipeline. `DINOForge.Runtime` is built `netstandard2.0` outside the editor (`dotnet build`), so codegen never replaces the lambda placeholder and it throws at runtime — flooding the log every simulation frame once `SimulationSystemGroup` ticks. Fixed by rewriting all three `OnUpdate` methods to the established manual `EntityQuery` pattern (cache the query in `OnCreate` with `EntityQueryOptions.IncludePrefab`, iterate `ToEntityArray(Allocator.Temp)`, `EntityManager.Get/SetComponentData`) — the same codegen-free approach used by `EntityQueries.cs` / `AssetSwapSystem.cs`. No `Entities.ForEach`/`Job.WithCode` remains anywhere in `src/Runtime/Aviation/`. Behavior (altitude lerp, nearest-enemy targeting, spawn-at-altitude, anti-air building sweep) is preserved exactly.
