docs\TRUTH_TABLE.md:1368:**Lens-rotation methodology validation, iteration 34**: convergence remains structurally local (each new lens still finds *something*), but the *type* of finding has shifted from semantic bugs to debuggability/observability concerns (LogError stack loss is a classic obs-debt finding). This shift is itself a signal that production correctness is in better shape than 30 iterations ago — earlier iterations were finding real semantic defects (deadlocks, path injection, AssetSwap 0/36); recent iterations are finding "would have helped if X had been better" concerns.
